column1: Gross enrolment ratio, pre-primary (% of preschool-age children)
SDG 4.2 By 2030, ensure that all girls and boys have access to quality early childhood development,care and pre-primary education so that they are ready for primary education

Definition: Total enrolment in a given level of education (pre-primary, primary, secondary or tertiary), regardless of age, expressed as a percentage of the official school-age population for the same level of education.
Source: UNESCO (United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) Institute for Statistics (2020). Data Centre. http://data.uis.unesco.org. Accessed 21 July 2020.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development

column1: a: Data refer to the most recent year available during the period specified.
